34:52.122 --> 34:53.564
It happens like that in our Christian life.

34:56.848 --> 34:58.250
We can think that God disappeared.

34:59.572 --> 35:01.134
Where's the love in our relationship?

35:01.395 --> 35:05.180
Husbands and wives will talk about that, especially as they go through midlife.

35:05.200 --> 35:06.842
They'll have those kinds of conversations.

35:07.503 --> 35:08.244
It's not the same.

35:08.304 --> 35:13.751
Here's what we can do in marriages.

35:14.011 --> 35:16.615
Acknowledge the presence of your spouse.

35:17.937 --> 35:18.898
It's kind of the same thing.

35:21.026 --> 35:30.055
That love relationship that you had with the Lord at the beginning was so powerful and so strong, but it can seem like in the valley that God has says, you're on your own on this one.

35:31.076 --> 35:31.797
He's not like that.

35:33.699 --> 35:35.581
He just wants you to acknowledge that he's there.

35:37.983 --> 35:39.004
You're saying, but I don't see him.

35:41.006 --> 35:41.647
I don't feel him.

35:44.089 --> 35:44.670
I don't hear him.

35:46.071 --> 35:46.492
What do I do?

35:47.793 --> 35:48.914
What am I asking you to do?

35:50.690 --> 35:52.072
Just acknowledge Him still.

35:53.815 --> 35:54.636
Still acknowledge Him.

35:57.201 --> 35:58.583
And He will manifest.

36:00.686 --> 36:01.267
He will show.

36:03.811 --> 36:04.593
He'll speak to you.

36:06.075 --> 36:07.016
He'll reveal to you.

36:07.597 --> 36:08.759
Listen to this in Psalm 46.

36:08.940 --> 36:10.682
I want to look at just verse 1 to 11.

36:10.702 --> 36:11.504
You don't have to turn there.

36:11.844 --> 36:13.106
God is our refuge and strength.

36:13.126 --> 36:15.410
They're very present, help and trouble.

36:15.778 --> 36:17.901
Therefore, we will not fear through the earth gives way.

36:17.941 --> 36:19.984
The mountains be moved into the heart of the sea.

36:20.404 --> 36:23.689
Its waters roar and foam through the mountains tremble at its swelling.

36:24.289 --> 36:29.316
There is a river whose stream makes glad the city of God the holy habitation of the Most High.

36:29.817 --> 36:31.259
God is in the midst of her.

36:32.861 --> 36:34.063
God is in the midst of her.

36:34.143 --> 36:35.464
She shall not be moved.

36:36.105 --> 36:37.928
God will help her when mourning dawns.

36:38.028 --> 36:38.969
The nation is raged.

36:38.989 --> 36:39.910
The kingdom's totter.

36:40.631 --> 36:42.454
He utters his voice.

36:42.474 --> 36:43.435
The earth melts.

36:43.876 --> 36:45.618
The Lord of hosts is with us.

36:45.794 --> 36:47.196
The Lord of hosts is with us.

36:49.780 --> 36:51.643
The God of Jacob is our fortress.

36:54.106 --> 36:58.253
Come behold, the works of the Lord, how he has brought desolations on the earth.

36:59.394 --> 37:03.901
Oh, the Lord is with us here right now.

37:07.186 --> 37:07.707
He's with us.

37:08.788 --> 37:09.409
Acknowledge it.

37:10.351 --> 37:15.378
Number four, finally, allow God's purposes to be fulfilled, your rod,

37:15.522 --> 37:17.305
and your staff, they comfort me.

37:18.426 --> 37:19.628
The rod was for correction.

37:19.708 --> 37:21.491
The staff is for protection.

37:22.452 --> 37:25.116
Both are descriptive of God's purposes in our lives.

37:26.098 --> 37:27.400
Comfort and correction.

37:27.720 --> 37:29.202
Comfort and correction.

37:31.866 --> 37:33.809
This is something that we need to allow.

37:34.070 --> 37:35.031
Allow God to do this.

37:35.091 --> 37:36.093
Allow God to correct you.

37:37.014 --> 37:38.777
Does anybody need correction this morning?

37:40.439 --> 37:40.960
Seriously.

37:41.240 --> 37:42.322
It's like we all get there.

37:43.810 --> 37:44.992
Does anybody need comfort?

37:45.012 --> 37:48.376
You're saying, yeah, I need lots of comfort, but not so much the correction piece.

37:50.720 --> 37:51.821
How about you take both of them?

37:53.283 --> 37:55.467
This is how allowing God's purposes in our life.

37:55.547 --> 37:56.248
David knew that.

37:57.369 --> 38:00.233
Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.

38:01.215 --> 38:01.816
Let me close.

38:02.937 --> 38:05.240
I gotta have you turn to Luke chapter three, and this will be it.

38:05.761 --> 38:07.524
Luke chapter three in our New Testament.

38:07.544 --> 38:08.625
I won't kid around with you.

38:08.645 --> 38:09.887
It's definitely in the New Testament.

38:10.868 --> 38:12.050
So go to Luke three.

38:13.378 --> 38:15.561
There's a TV show that Lisa and I have watched for years.

38:15.641 --> 38:16.262
It's called 2020.

38:16.642 --> 38:18.965
You might be familiar with that.

38:19.045 --> 38:22.970
It's that show they solve mysteries and all that kind of thing.

38:24.131 --> 38:30.539
And so you watch that and it's interesting to go through the episode of 2020 and you get to the end and you're like, oh, now I see.

38:30.880 --> 38:32.602
Now I understand who the person was.

38:32.622 --> 38:33.563
I did that to the other.

38:34.484 --> 38:37.828
But God is doing that in all of our lives spiritually.

38:37.848 --> 38:42.674
He's bringing us to 2020 vision in the middle of the valleys of life.

38:44.130 --> 38:47.856
But I want to bring some encouragement as I close Luke chapter three verse four.

38:49.879 --> 38:50.220
Amazing.

38:51.682 --> 39:03.381
As it is written, book the words of Isaiah the prophet, the voice of one crying in the wilderness prepared the way of the Lord.

39:04.223 --> 39:05.164
Who's that referring to?

39:05.385 --> 39:05.725
Anybody know?

39:07.508 --> 39:08.690
John the Baptist, yeah.

39:10.466 --> 39:16.154
and make His past straight, every valley shall be filled.

39:17.696 --> 39:18.176
Interesting.

39:19.558 --> 39:24.084
Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be made low.

39:24.705 --> 39:33.437
And the crooked shall become straight, and the rough places shall become level ways, and all flesh shall see the salvation of God.

39:33.958 --> 39:37.042
Some of you need to see the salvation of God.

39:39.138 --> 39:40.701
The valleys are going to be filled.

39:41.101 --> 39:48.133
How do the valleys get filled in the Messiah, in Yeshua, in Jesus Christ, in the gospel?

39:50.177 --> 39:54.044
So you're in a valley, whether you're a Christian or a non-Christian.

39:54.064 --> 39:55.847
Can I talk to the non-Christian really quick?

39:57.510 --> 39:58.612
You're not a believer yet.

39:59.673 --> 40:04.722
You haven't repented of your sins and put your full faith in Jesus Christ, dying on a cross for you.

40:05.602 --> 40:08.186
You haven't asked them into your life and say, would you forgive me?

40:08.206 --> 40:10.209
I just want to follow you the rest of my days.

40:11.411 --> 40:12.232
You haven't done that.

40:13.354 --> 40:15.156
Then your valley will not be filled.

40:20.344 --> 40:23.148
This deep darkness will only get darker for you.

40:25.051 --> 40:28.836
Total and complete separation from a holy God for all eternity.

40:29.417 --> 40:29.998
That'll be you.

40:31.520 --> 40:32.562
It doesn't have to be.

40:36.706 --> 40:42.375
John the Baptist came as a forerunner to Christ the Messiah, pointing people to Jesus.

40:43.698 --> 40:46.663
Any pastor or preacher now points people to Jesus.

40:46.763 --> 40:50.048
I'm pointing you to Jesus and the gospel.

40:50.489 --> 40:52.112
Will you be born again?

40:53.454 --> 40:54.756
Will you accept Him today?

40:56.459 --> 40:58.222
You're saying, I've been running for far too long.

40:58.242 --> 40:59.043
Well, stop running.

40:59.063 --> 41:00.786
Today's the day of your salvation.

41:06.978 --> 41:08.680
Jesus is the one that fills the valley.

41:11.163 --> 41:13.805
He's there for you Christians that are going through some stuff.

41:14.847 --> 41:15.768
I totally understand.

41:18.410 --> 41:20.272
And you're going to be uncertain about the next turn.

41:20.312 --> 41:22.415
You're going to be uncertain about where this is leading.

41:22.435 --> 41:24.397
That's all okay.

41:26.679 --> 41:27.720
It's going to take some time.

41:29.763 --> 41:34.007
I want your vision in the valley to get stronger and clear 2020 vision.

41:35.989 --> 41:36.530
Accept.

41:37.346 --> 41:38.588
Here it is, application.

41:39.970 --> 41:41.091
Accept the path of pain.

41:43.034 --> 41:44.636
Aggressively put fear in its place.

41:46.739 --> 41:48.021
Don't let it paralyze you anymore.

41:50.565 --> 41:56.733
Acknowledge the presence of God and allow God's purposes to be fulfilled.

41:56.753 --> 41:57.634
You do those four things?

41:58.816 --> 41:59.898
Your vision is going to get better.

42:01.139 --> 42:01.920
We praise you, Lord.

42:01.960 --> 42:02.802
We give you glory.

42:03.663 --> 42:05.906
You're such a great and awesome and mighty God.

42:06.530 --> 42:13.798
This valley or gorge that we're going through, oh, I pray, God, that you would just continue to pour out your blessing, your grace, your mercies.

42:13.878 --> 42:14.719
They're new every morning.

42:15.540 --> 42:19.464
Even this morning, Lord, mercy was being poured out given to people.

42:20.285 --> 42:21.206
Thank you, Lord, for that.

42:21.226 --> 42:23.609
Thank you for the path of pain.

42:23.649 --> 42:24.249
We accept it.

42:25.591 --> 42:25.851
We do.

42:25.931 --> 42:27.253
We want to be aggressive against fear.

42:28.053 --> 42:28.894
I will fear no evil.

42:30.276 --> 42:32.298
We want to acknowledge your presence.

42:32.318 --> 42:35.922
We want to allow your purposes to be fulfilled in this valley.

42:36.642 --> 42:37.684
Our vision is getting better.

42:37.944 --> 42:38.985
We thank you Lord for that.

42:39.827 --> 42:41.549
Help us to continue to get stronger.

42:42.751 --> 42:44.073
May things become more clear.

42:45.415 --> 42:53.987
And when those are in the valley right now, maybe listening, you know, watch this online sometime in the future and they're going through some stuff that is just beyond belief.

42:54.488 --> 42:57.632
You can't even imagine the depth of the pain.

42:57.672 --> 42:58.473
Oh, that was David.

42:58.534 --> 43:01.217
David had absolutely betrayed him and eventually was killed.

43:02.680 --> 43:04.402
Such a heartbreaking thing for David.

43:05.794 --> 43:08.958
I pray for the hearts that are breaking in this room.

43:10.659 --> 43:12.461
May they have a clear vision of who you are.

43:13.803 --> 43:16.146
They're going to see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living.

43:16.226 --> 43:17.487
That's what your word says.

43:18.388 --> 43:19.129
And I pray over them.

43:19.189 --> 43:20.470
We pray over them as a church.

43:21.972 --> 43:22.973
Thank you, Lord, for today.

43:23.414 --> 43:25.556
We pray that you were pleased and honored and glorified.

43:26.337 --> 43:27.598
Thank you for speaking to us.

43:30.682 --> 43:32.464
How about we read Psalm 23 out loud.

43:32.484 --> 43:33.245
